      • binarySearch

        public static <X extends Number,Y extends Number> int binarySearch(ChartData<X,Y> data,
                                                                   double x)
        Searches the specified ChartData for the data point with specified X coordinate using the binary search algorithm. Points in the given ChartData must be sorted. This method is an equivalent of Arrays.binarySearch(double[], double) but dedicated to ChartData.
        Type Parameters:
        X - X value type
        Y - Y value type
        Parameters:
        data - the searched data
        x - X coordinate whose index should be returned
        Returns:
        index of the search X value, if it is contained in the ChartData; otherwise, (-(insertion point) - 1). The insertion point is defined as the point at which the key would be inserted into the data: the index of the first element greater than the X, or data.size() if all elements in the array are less than the specified X. Note that this guarantees that the return value will be >= 0 if and only if the X is found.
        See Also:
        Arrays.binarySearch(double[], double)
